sub_topic: Identifying the isomorphism between two graphs.
message_1: Consider two undirected graphs G and H, where G has 6 vertices and 7 edges, and H has 6 vertices and 6 edges. Determine if G and H are isomorphic, and if so, provide an isomorphism between them.
message_2: G and H cannot be isomorphic because they have a different number of edges. Isomorphic graphs must have the same number of vertices and edges, as well as the same degree sequence. Since G has 7 edges and H has 6 edges, they cannot be isomorphic, and there is no isomorphism between them.
